Dr Barney Selebane has been placed on precautionary suspension after he was named in the Health Ombudsman's report. JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng Premier David Makhura has suspended the Health Department s HOD following the damning Health Ombudsman's report on the deaths of 94 mentally ill patients in the province.Dr Barney Selebano has been placed on precautionary suspension after he was named in the report on the department s handling of the moving of the patients from Life Esidimeni facilities last year.At the same time, the Director of Mental Health Makgabo Manamela has been served with a notice of intention to suspend her in line with Health Ombudsman Malegapuru Makgoba s recommendations.Makgoba found that the senior officials and former MEC Qedani Mahlangu were reckless and negligent in their actions.Spokesperson for the Gauteng government Thabo Masebe said: The premier has suspended Dr Selebano and the suspension is with immediate effect. This is in line with the recommendations of the Health Ombudsman. Christa Eybers | A timeline of the events leading up to deaths of 94 psychiatric patients from Life Esidimeni, and the subsequent investigations.(Edited by Winnie Theletsane)